Durban - The father of Sadia Sukhraj, who was murdered during a botched hijacking last year, has began delivering his victim impact statement in the Durban High Court ahead of the sentencing of Sibonelo Seni Mkhize. The 39-year-old Savannah Park resident was found guilty of two counts of murder and armed robbery relating to May 2018 death of Sadia. The 9-year-old had been seated in her father's car when hijackers pounced making of with her in the vehicle. A shoot-out ensued and she was shot and later succumbed to her injuries in hospital. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
